Package: kwin-effect-moonglass
Architecture: any
# KWin effects have no stable ABI; pin to the KWin this was built against so apt
# rebuilds/updates the two together instead of loading a mismatched binary.
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, kwin-wayland (>= ${source:Upstream-Version})
Description: Luminance-keyed window transparency for KWin (Plasma 6)
 Moonglass fades each window pixel by its brightness: dark pixels become
 transparent and bright pixels (text, UI accents) stay opaque, so a window's
 background dissolves into the desktop while its content floats on top.
 .
 Unlike uniform window transparency it keys on per-pixel luminance, and clips
 windows behind a Moonglass window so transparent areas reveal the desktop.
